# test-microservice-backend architecture

This document describes the intended architecture of the **test-microservice-backend** service (Node.js + TypeScript + Express) as implemented in this repository.

## What this service does

`test-microservice-backend` powers the Tests/Quiz/Submission domain and provides both HTTP APIs and real-time features.

- REST API is mounted under `/api/v1`.
- Socket.IO is attached to the HTTP server.
- Kafka consumers are started during boot.

The service follows the repo layering pattern:

- **Routes** → **Controllers** → **Services** → **Repositories**

## Runtime entrypoints

- `src/server.ts`
  - Loads environment (`dotenv`).
  - Creates an HTTP server and attaches Socket.IO (`setupSocketIO`).
  - Starts Kafka workers (fetch/submit/rating).
  - Optionally configures a Redis adapter for Socket.IO when Redis connection details are available.
  - Listens on `PORT` (defaults to `5500`).
  - Handles graceful shutdown.

- `src/app.ts`
  - Builds the Express app.
  - Configures CORS, JSON/urlencoded parsing, cookies.
  - Installs request logging middleware (`logRequest`).
  - Mounts router at `/api/v1`.

## Request lifecycle

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  A[Client] -->|HTTP| B[Express app.ts]
  B --> C[Middleware chain]
  C --> D[Router: /api/v1]
  D --> E[Controller]
  E --> F[Service]
  F --> G[Repository]
  G --> H[(Postgres via Prisma)]
  G --> I[(Redis cache)]
  G --> K[gRPC clients]
  E -->|JSON| A

  A -->|WebSocket| W[Socket.IO]
  W --> I

  subgraph Kafka[Kafka workers]
    KW[Consumers] --> KS[Services/Repos]
  end
```

## Key modules and boundaries

- Routing: `src/routes/`
- Controllers: `src/controllers/`
- Services: `src/services/`
- Repositories: `src/repositories/`
- Middleware: `src/middlewares/`
- Validation: `src/validations/`
- Kafka workers: `src/utils/Kafka/Workers/`
- Socket.IO setup: `src/config/socket`

## Data & integrations

- Database: Postgres via Prisma (`prisma/schema.prisma`).
- Kafka: `kafkajs` consumers started at boot.
- Redis (mandatory): used for caching in repositories and (optionally) as the Socket.IO Redis adapter.
- gRPC: protos and clients exist under `src/grpc/`.

## Configuration & environment variables

Common env vars (exact usage may vary):

- Server: `PORT`, `ENV`, `DOMAIN`
- DB: `DATABASE_URL`
- Auth: `TOKEN_SECRET`
- Redis (socket adapter): `REDIS_URL`
- Kafka: `KAFKA_BROKERS`, `KAFKA_CLIENT_ID`, topic names as used by workers
- gRPC: `GRPC_HOST`, `GRPC_PORT`

